@tubewatcher97 It's relatively easy to convince someone to loan you $100 if you promise to give them $110 back. It's a lot harder to convince someone to lend you $1000 if you are only promising to give them $1010 back.

That's because it's a much bigger risk to lend someone $1000 then it is to lend them $100. Now scale that up to hundreds of millions of dollars.

People typically expect profit to be based on a percentage of the money they lend, not a constant value independent of the amount loaned. As such marketing budgets also often end up being based on a percentage of the project budget rather then a constant value independent from it.

